response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Maximum Sum of Divisors\", \"description\": \"Given an integer n, find the maximum sum of divisors of all numbers from 1 to n. A divisor of a number is an integer that divides the number without leaving a remainder.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer representing the upper bound.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of divisors of all numbers from 1 to n.\", \"code\": \"\\ndef max_sum_of_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n    def sum_of_divisors(num: int) -> int:\\n        return sum(i for i in range(1, num + 1) if num % i == 0)\\n\\n    return max(sum_of_divisors(i) for i in range(1, n + 1))\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert max_sum_of_divisors(10) == 18\", \"assert max_sum_of_divisors(20) == 42\", \"assert max_sum_of_divisors(30) == 76\"] }"
